General_Information.Name: Flint
General_Information.Description: A hard sedimentary rock that chips when struck by a hard object, forming sharp cutting edges.
General_Information.FlavorText: A hard sedimentary rock that chips away with ease, forming sharp edges. Used in crafting.

Discovery.AdditionalInformation:: Jagged rock that can be found anywhere on ocean beaches and near river beds. You could ask someone who knows about mining in town to learn more.
Discovery.QuestUnlocked:: Ask a Mining Trainer in a Mine for more information
Discovery.Trainer:: Ah, the versatile flint. It's a brittle rock that can be broken down into large or small pieces with sharp edges. It's pretty common around the island. You know you can find these near any river, right?
Discovery.Discovery3Text: If I tie multiple sharp short sticks of this wood with some rope, I can manufacture a large foot trap that can be quite deadly. It's going to be a nasty surprise for anyone that put his best foot forward.

Tooltips.SubHeader2Text: A hard sedimentary rock that chips when struck by a hard object, forming sharp cutting edges.

Discovery.AdditionalInformation:: A tender and aromatic herb with a bushy and small fragrant leaves. You could ask someone who knows about plants in town to learn more.
Discovery.QuestUnlocked:: Ask a Herb Gathering Trainer in a Hospital for more information
Discovery.Trainer:: Ahhh the fragrance i would recognize it anywhere. What you have there is Basilicum, if you were to grind it to a fine paste it can be used as an ointment on wounds. On top of that if you have some Banana Leaves they will hold the medicine in place and protect the wound, which we call a Primitive Bandage.

Tooltips.SubHeader2Text: A plant with potentially healing properties.

General_Information.Name: Sea Bird
General_Information.Description: Small biplane that has a parallel set pair of wings and a fish shaped fuselage with the engine protruding in the front.
General_Information.FlavorText: The engineers of Jentzen Industires were so convinced in the prototype's operational reliability even with minimal testing, that they encouraged Claus Jentzen the owner and CEO of the company and a pilot enthusiast, to perform a testflight himself. He recognized the potential and versatility of the airborne vehicle, so he adopted one of the prototypes as his personal means of quick travel between the many company owned factory lines

Taking notes and organizing files was not his forte, which is why he hired trained staff after all. So he requested the engineers to develop the Sea-Bird plane further so that they could add another seat on the plane. The modification of the airplane's fuselage was arduous, but the engineers managed to install a passenger seat without sacrificing too much of the plane's performance.

General_Information.Name: Sparrow
General_Information.Description: This biplane has the fuselage mounted between the wings, with a gap between the lower longerons and the wing, along with a substantial part of the fin beneath the fuselage.
General_Information.FlavorText: Trying to develop a biplane that would set a new airspeed record almost took Robertson Aeronautics under. The constant engine failure drained the development funds to the very edge of bankruptcy before the marketing team managed to find an adequate solution. The latest stable engine was installed and the plane was repurposed to serve as the country's postal service vehicle for fast mailing and delivery.

The near bankruptcy left all of the company's departments fearful of new innovative endeavors. Luckily the postal service needed some improvements on the carrying capacity of the Sparrow biplane. A small but inspirational challenge for the engineers of the company. They acmoplished the task with relative ease and modified the Sparrow biplane to carry additional cargo or a person. More importantly, this sparked their flame for research and development to push the limits of science and technology even further.

General_Information.Description: Desert biplane with a modified fuselage to hold and extra passenger.
General_Information.FlavorText: The intended design of the Desert biplane proved an exceptional basis for its new repurposed functionality. The aerial application in agriculture was a tremendous improvement that stimulated the development and the use of much larger fertile surfaces. It prompted a necessity to improve the carrying capacity of the Desert biplane to hold more pesticides or fertilizer. Kowalski Ltd. distributed the upgraded variant to the agricultural companies and the Forest Service, which already have used the previous model. The forest wardens asked for a slight redesign of the biplane. Namely, they wanted a second seat installed in the biplane to increase scouting performance and to have a more reliable lead plane to coordinate firefighting operations.

General_Information.Name: Fox
General_Information.Description: This triplane design allows for a shorter fuselage and a shorter wingspan without sacrificing speed or maneuverability.
General_Information.FlavorText: The international project cooperation between Sorim Engineering, a company that produces engines for heavy machinery, and Shtochkin Avionics, which at the time was mourning the untimely passing of Vasilij Shtochkin, lead designer, founder, and CEO, was an unorthodox move. The company leadership was succeeded by his daughter, who following in her father's footsteps, was getting her engineering degree. The revolutionary design of the Fox triplane made people very excited. But the result of Sorim-Shtochkina's first product was profoundly mediocre and was mockingly dubbed the So-So, although everyone admitted that it looked cool.

General_Information.Name: Fox II
General_Information.Description: Fox triplane with a modified fuselage to hold an extra passenger.
General_Information.FlavorText: As the development of the Fox triplane progressed, Yelena Shtochkina often tried to convince Tae Sorim to take flying lessons and experience the freedom of flight and the adrenaline rush of soaring through the open skies. Tae, a slightly older gentleman who has witnessed the early development of aviation technology, was very reluctant to do so. To overcome this, Yelena diverted some funds to develop a prototype of the Fox triplane with a passenger seat. Now she only needed to convince Tae to take a ride with her. To achieve this, she cleverly proposed a bet that if the Fox single-seater triplane achieved the top speed record over the current market competition, Tae would have to accompany her on a flight. Needless to say that Mr. Sorim overly enjoyed his first but not only flight with the triplane, and the companies had a prototype ready to compete with the current market demand for double-seater aircraft.

General_Information.Name: Zephyr
General_Information.Description: Large passenger aircraft with 4 engines that are placed on each side of the underwing nacelles with a back to back configuration. The front engine poweres a two-bladed propeller and the rear engine a three-bladed one.
General_Information.FlavorText: Graeme McLafferty was working as an aerodynamical engineer at Robertson Aeronautics. McLafferty constantly asked himself a crucial question: "Can we make airplanes bigger?" In his spare time, he was trying to answer this question by designing a colossal airplane that could potentially carry a large number of passengers and traverse great distances. Presenting the idea to the CEO was a scary notion, with the company's recent past. But he did it anyway. John Robertson III, the CEO of Robertson Aeronautics, immediately recognized the potential of this development but was also aware of the sizeable investment that the project required. John Robertson, an innovator at heart, invited the top brass of Kowalski LTD, Jentzen Industries, and Shtochkin Avionics for a presentation of the project. With great enthusiasm and excitement, they all agreed that each company would devote its best qualities to the challenging project and divide the profits of each unit sold equally.

Discovery.Trainer:: Very tall palm tree wirh pretty green leaves that create a lovely shade. The Coconut Tree usually has fruit and most people just climb the tree with ease just to collect it. You can cut it down if you need to, with some effort and get a Coconut Trunk to go along with the Coconut Leaves and the Coconut.

Discovery.AdditionalInformation:: A tropical plant that produces large leaves and bears fruit. Looks like it can be cut down with ease. You could ask someone who knows more about wood in town to learn more.
Discovery.QuestUnlocked:: Ask a Woodcutting Trainer in a Carpentry for more information
Discovery.Trainer:: Few things on the island are as handy as this tree. It's fruits are good to fill your stomach when you are hungry and its stem can be fashioned into various items if you have some tools on hand. Be on the lookout for this tree while you are galavanting around on the Island.

General_Information.Name: Bamboo Tree
General_Information.Description: A tall, woody grass that grows in tropical and subtropical regions and is known for its fast growth and versatility as a building and crafting material.

Discovery.AdditionalInformation:: Tall, hollow, and flexible tree that can be found around the island. You could ask someone who knows more about wood in town to learn more.
Discovery.Drop:: Bamboo Trunk, Bamboo Short Stick, Bamboo Long Stick
Discovery.QuestUnlocked:: Ask a Woodcutting Trainer in a Carpentry for more information
Discovery.Trainer:: It's tall, hollow, and flexible. Most people call it Bamboo Tree, but it is a perennial grass with a slender culm that has numerous practical uses. If you apply yourself in the right way with the right tool you will get Bamboo Trunk, Bamboo Long Stick and Bamboo Short Stick.

General_Information.Name: Banyan Tree
General_Information.Description: A large, tropical tree that is characterized by its aerial roots that grow downwards and form additional trunks.

Discovery.AdditionalInformation:: A massive and gnarled evergreen tree that supports numerous hanging vines. You could ask someone who knows more about wood in town to learn more.
Discovery.Drop:: Banyan Trunk, Banyan Short Stick, Liana, Banyan Long Stick
Discovery.QuestUnlocked:: Ask a Woodcutting Trainer in a Carpentry for more information
Discovery.Trainer:: Banyan tree, or banian we call ‘em. Usually found in the rainforest, right in the thick of it! A nice soft easy to work with tree, usually got them liana vines on ‘em. They drop a variety of resources, like Banyan Trunk's, Banyan Short Stick and Bunyan Long Sticks.

General_Information.Name: Araucaria Pine Tree

Discovery.AdditionalInformation:: Tall, strong and towering evergreen tree covered with blisters of a dark sticky substance. You could ask someone who knows more about wood in town to learn more.
Discovery.Drop:: Araucaria Trunk, Araucaria Leaves, Araucaria Short Stick, Araucaria Long Stick
Discovery.QuestUnlocked:: Ask a Woodcutting Trainer in a Carpentry for more information

They are just beautiful, tall, strong, and towering evergreen trees that can have blisters of Resin on their bark. I am told they can be found higher up in the mountains, and if you manage to cut one down it will yield an Araucaria Trunk, Araucaria Leaves, Araucaria Long Stick, and Araucaria Short Stick.

Discovery.Trainer:: Banana Leaves can be very usefull in the wild. If you sometimes need to improvise a shelter in the wilderness you can stack the leaves over the wooden construction that you have and they will obstruct the rain and wind, for the most part. With the leftover leaves you can make a primitive bandage by adding some crushed Basilicum and wrap it over the wound. The leaf will hold the medicine in place and protect the wound from external contaminants while healing.
Discovery.Discovery3Text: With some medicinal salve, some banana leaves and rope of any kind can be combined into a primitive bandage.

Discovery.AdditionalInformation:: Straight and cylindrical trunk with a rough bark and blisters of a dark sticky substance. You could ask someone who knows more about wood in town to learn more.
Discovery.QuestUnlocked:: Ask a Woodcutting Trainer in a Carpentry for more information
Discovery.Trainer:: Hey, i love working with an Araucaria Trunk. It's straight and cylindrical with a rough bark covered with blisters of Resin, commonly used as high-density and heavy-weight crafting material for melee weapons, firearms and utility items. We cut them down to Araucaria Logs, but first we remove the Resin from the bark.

Tooltips.SubHeader2Text: Straight and cylindrical trunk with a rough bark and blisters of a dark sticky substance. You could ask someone who knows more about wood in town to learn more.

Discovery.AdditionalInformation:: Long pieces of wood cut from a Araucaria tree. You could ask someone who knows more about wood in town to learn more.
Discovery.QuestUnlocked:: Ask a Woodcutting Trainer in a Carpentry for more information
Discovery.Trainer:: If you throw some of these pieces of wood they will keep the fire stoked for a long time.

General_Information.Name: Araucaria Short Stick
General_Information.Description: A short, cylindrical piece of wood from a Araucaria tree.

Discovery.AdditionalInformation:: A small, cylindrical piece of Arucaria wood. Could have many potential uses. You could ask someone who knows more about weapons in town to learn more.
Discovery.QuestUnlocked:: Ask a Weaponsmith Trainer in a Weapon Workshop for more information
Discovery.Trainer:: Well this is a fine piece of wood, you can do a lot with this one. If you sharpen the stick it can serve as ammunition for any bow but if you have a nice piece of sharp flint you can make a knife, and if you tie it this way you can make an axe or a better arrow with a flint tip.
Discovery.Discovery3Text: If I tie it this way you can make an axe or a better arrow with a Flint tip.

Tooltips.SubHeader2Text: A short, cylindrical piece of wood from a Araucaria tree.

General_Information.Name: Araucaria Long Stick
General_Information.Description: A long, cylindrical piece of wood from a Araucaria tree.

Discovery.AdditionalInformation:: A long, cylindrical piece of wood from a Araucaria tree. You could ask someone who knows more about weapons in town to learn more.
Discovery.QuestUnlocked:: Ask a Weaponsmith Trainer in a Weapon Workshop for more information
Discovery.Trainer:: You can fashion a basic wooden spear when its tip its sharpened with a Sharp Tool, but if you have an elongated piece of Sharp Flint and some Rope you can creat a better spear.
Discovery.Discovery3Text: If you have some rope and a piece of Flint it will make for a nice spear.

Tooltips.SubHeader2Text: A long, cylindrical piece of wood from a Araucaria tree.

General_Information.Name: Queen Palm Trunk
General_Information.Description: Slender trunk with a grey and smooth bark.

Discovery.AdditionalInformation:: Slender trunk with a grey and smooth bark. You could ask someone who knows more about wood in town to learn more.
Discovery.Drop:: Queen Palm Heart, Queen Palm Log
Discovery.QuestUnlocked:: Ask a Woodcutting Trainer in a Carpentry for more information
Discovery.Trainer:: That is a slender trunk of a Queen Palm with a grey and smooth bark containing an edible core which with a bit of effort is quite tasty.
Discovery.Discovery3Text: If you are not hungry then you can extract curved and light crafting materials with elastic properties.

Tooltips.SubHeader2Text: Slender trunk with a grey and smooth bark.

General_Information.Name: Banyan Trunk
General_Information.Description: A thick and massive gnarled trunk, with reddish-brown bark.

Discovery.AdditionalInformation:: A thick and massive gnarled trunk, with reddish-brown bark. You could ask someone who knows more about wood in town to learn more.
Discovery.QuestUnlocked:: Ask a Woodcutting Trainer in a Carpentry for more information
Discovery.Trainer:: The Banyan Trunk is gnarled, thick and massive, with reddish-brown bark that makes this tree stand out from the rest of the flora. We cut the donw to Banyan Log's before additional refinement.

Tooltips.SubHeader2Text: A thick and massive gnarled trunk, with reddish-brown bark.

General_Information.Description: Long pieces of wood cut from a Banyan tree.

Discovery.AdditionalInformation:: Long pieces of wood cut from a Banyan tree. You could ask someone who knows more about wood in town to learn more.
Discovery.QuestUnlocked:: Ask a Woodcutting Trainer in a Carpentry for more information
Discovery.Trainer:: A good fuel to keep the fire going during long sleepless nights in the jungle. Just chop one down and chuck it into the fire and whats sparks fly!

General_Information.Name: Banyan Short Stick
General_Information.Description: A short, cylindrical piece of wood from a Banyan tree.

Discovery.AdditionalInformation:: A small, cylindrical piece of banyan wood. Could have many potential uses. You could ask someone who knows about weapons in town to learn more.
Discovery.QuestUnlocked:: Ask a Weaponsmith Trainer in a Weapon Workshop for more information
Discovery.Trainer:: This is good material to work with. You can sharpen it with any sharp tool into a fine point and use it as ammunition for your bow.
Discovery.Discovery3Text: Attaching a sharp piece of flint to it with some rope to make a knife seems like a good idea. Its going to come in handy either way.

Tooltips.SubHeader2Text: A short, cylindrical piece of wood from a Banyan tree.

General_Information.Name: Queen Palm Long Stick
General_Information.Description: A long, curved, cylindrical piece of wood from a Queen Palm tree

Discovery.AdditionalInformation:: A long, curved, cylindrical piece of wood from a Queen Palm tree. Could have many potential uses. You could ask someone who knows more about weapons in town to learn more.
Discovery.QuestUnlocked:: Ask a Weaponsmith Trainer in a Weapon Workshop for more information
Discovery.Trainer:: Quite elastic material, and it is easy to find a piece that has a natural curve. This makes it a good choice for making a Bow, you just need a Rope to make the bowstring and brace it.
Discovery.Discovery3Text: Fastening a piece of flint with some rope on this long stick will make a spear. Keeping things at a distance is a smart way of fighting in this place.

Tooltips.SubHeader2Text: A long, curved, cylindrical piece of wood from a Queen Palm tree

General_Information.Name: Banyan Long Stick
General_Information.Description: A long, cylindrical piece of banyan wood.

Discovery.AdditionalInformation:: A long, cylindrical piece of wood from a Banyan tree. You could ask someone who knows about weapons in town to learn more.
Discovery.QuestUnlocked:: Ask a Weaponsmith Trainer in a Weapon Workshop for more information
Discovery.Trainer:: Not the best and not the worst material to be found in the jungle. Its tip can be sharpened with a sharp tool and used as a simple spear weapon.
Discovery.Discovery3Text: If I make some rope from the Liana so it can tie and hold a sharp flint at the tip and make a spear.
